parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy during a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays or failures in addressing airbag recalls can lead to continued risk of injury or death from faulty airbags.
The illumination of the SRS light can indicate a malfunction in the airbag system, which can lead to unexpected airbag deployment or failure to deploy in a crash.
Premature brake wear and failure can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise when applying the brakes
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
vehicle wobbles or shakes when braking
rotors need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Paint Defect and Clear Coat Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The paint defect and clear coat failure can lead to rusting of the metal parts, which can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, especially in accidents. Additionally, the peeling paint can expose the underlying metal, causing rust and corrosion, which can lead to safety issues.
symptoms: The paint is peeling or chipping off
paint is coming off in circular patches

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the weatherproofing strips can cause water to leak into the interior of the vehicle, which can lead to electrical issues, rust, and corrosion, compromising the safety of the vehicle.
symptoms: The weatherproofing strips are melting and coming off
allowing water to leak into the door and potentially causing electrical issues.
